properties.description: In 2023, a total of 70 different species of birds were captured on video at Warbler Ridge. The compilation of these videos shows the birds in chronological order, starting from January and continuing through December. Most of the footage was filmed at the bird pond and other water features on the property, which is located in eastern Tennessee. The filming was done using a GoPro Hero 5 Black camera and a Canon 6D. The project aims to provide a healthy habitat for a variety of birds, with a focus on improving water sources and natural food and shelter for the upcoming year.
